2000-11-04  Theodore C. Belding  <streak@umich.edu>

* Released version 1.2.2
* Added bootstrap script to generate configure script

2000-11-02  Theodore C. Belding  <streak@umich.edu>

* Released version 1.2.1
* Minor configuration cleanup

2000-10-01  Theodore C. Belding  <streak@umich.edu>

* Released version 1.2
* Added RPM spec file
* Minor cleanups

2000-09-19  Theodore C. Belding  <streak@umich.edu>

* Added configure, config.h.in, and Makefile.in files to CVS
repository, for those who don't have automake or autoconf.
* Remove *~ *.bak in "make clean" target.

20000303 Version 1.1:

* Now using libtool, autoconf, and automake.
* fcmp now uses libtool's versioning system for shared libraries.
  The fcmp shared library's current interface number is now 2. From
  now on, the name of the fcmp shared library will not reflect the 
  release number of the fcmp package. For example, the shared library 
  for this release (1.1) of fcmp is named libfcmp.so.2.0.0, not 
  libfcmp.so.1.1.0.
* Added AUTHORS, THANKS, and ChangeLog files.
* Replaced INSTALL file with generic GNU INSTALL file; moved fcmp-
  specific installation info to the README file.
* Renamed COPYING.LIB to COPYING, to satisfy automake (fcmp is still 
  under the LGPL).

20000131 Version 1.0.3: 

* Rearranged documentation to follow GNU coding standards.
* Some documentation improvements.
* No need to upgrade from previous releases.

20000128 Version 1.0.2:

* Added SHAREDCFLAGS variable to Makefile, to fix shared library
  compilation problem on Solaris. (Harald H. Soleng)
* Some documentation improvements.

20000124 Version 1.0.1:

* First public release.
* Minor cleanups of documentation and Makefile.
* Moved CVS tree to SourceForge <http://sourceforge.net>.
* Added homepage and mailing list info to README.
* Updated copyright to 2000.

19990110 Version 1.0:

* First release.

